---
import { EventChart } from '@/components/charts/EventChart';
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { ArrowDown } from 'lucide-react';
---

<!-- Slide 1: Events Intro -->
<section id="events-intro" data-chapter="events-intro" data-nav-label="Chapter 2: Events" class="h-screen w-full flex items-center justify-center p-8 snap-start bg-secondary/20 relative">
     <div class="container max-w-4xl text-center space-y-8">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight lg:text-6xl">Chapter 2: Real World Impact</h2>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
            Reddit is not isolated from the physical world. <br/>
            When something major happens out there, it explodes in here.
        </p>
        <div class="pt-8">
            <a href="#events-chart">
                <Button variant="outline" size="lg" className="gap-2">
                    Observe the Spikes <ArrowDown className="h-4 w-4" />
                </Button>
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

 <!-- Slide 2: Events Chart & Analysis -->
<section id="events-chart" class="h-screen w-full flex items-center justify-center p-8 snap-start bg-background relative">
    <div class="container max-w-7xl grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
         <div class="w-full h-[60vh] flex items-center justify-center p-4 order-2 lg:order-1">
             <EventChart client:visible />
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-8 order-1 lg:order-2">
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold lg:text-4xl">The Digital Seismograph</h3>
             <div class="prose dark:prose-invert text-lg">
                <p>
                    Our system detects anomalies in link sharing and comment volume. 
                    Look at <strong>April 2023</strong> on the chart.
                </p>
                <p>
                    This massive spike isn't random. It corresponds precisely to the <strong>Reddit API Protests</strong>, 
                    where thousands of communities went dark or changed their posting rules.
                </p>
                <p>
                    This confirms that subreddit activity volume is a reliable proxy for real-world event impact monitoring.
                </p>
            </div>
             <a href="#stock-intro" class="inline-block pt-4">
                <Button variant="outline" className="gap-2">
                    Next Chapter: Markets <ArrowDown className="h-4 w-4" />
                </Button>
            </a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
